(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 Section 1000.21. A. 1. There is hereby created the Oklahoma
2 Uniform Building Code Commission within the Construction Industries
3 Board which shall consist of thirteen (13) members, eleven of whom
4 shall be appointed by the Governor with the advice and consent of
5 the Senate as follows:
6 a. one member who is a general contractor from a
7 statewide organization that represents residential
8 construction,
9 b. one member who is a general contractor from a
10 statewide organization that represents commercial
11 construction,
12 c. one member who is a contractor from a statewide
13 organization that represents electrical contractors,
14 d. one member who is a contractor from a statewide
15 organization that represents plumbing contractors,
16 e. one member who is a contractor from a statewide
17 organization that represents heating and cooling
18 contractors,
19 f. one member who is a licensed electrical engineer from
20 a state-recognized professional engineering firm,
21 g. one member who is a local-level regulator/inspector
22 who is a member of a statewide organization that is
23 exempt from taxation under federal law and designated
24 pursuant to the provisions of the Internal Revenue
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2085 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 Code of 1986, as amended, 26 U.S.C., Section 170(a),
2 who has represented municipalities and had statutory
3 functions for municipalities for at least fifteen (15)
4 ten (10) years prior to November 1, 2005,
5 h. one member who is a Certified Building Official
6 certified building official employed by a political
7 subdivision,
8 i. one member who is a licensed architect from a
9 statewide organization that represents architects,
10 j. one member who is from the insurance industry with
11 knowledge of building codes and experience in property
12 loss mitigation, and
13 k. one member who is a licensed mechanical engineer from
14 a state-recognized professional engineering firm.
15 2. The members shall be appointed for staggered terms of four
16 (4) years. The initial appointment of the members added by this act
17 shall be made within ninety (90) days of the effective date of this
18 act. A full term of office for purposes of determining term limits
19 provided in subsection C of this section shall be the completion of
20 a full four-year term of appointment.
21 B. The remaining two members of the Commission shall be the
22 State Fire Marshal, or a designee, and an appointee of the
23 Construction Industries Board.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2085 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 C. Appointed members shall continue in office until a successor
2 is appointed by the Governor, notwithstanding the term limitations.
3 No appointed member shall serve more than two consecutive full four-
4 year terms; provided, such a member shall be eligible to serve until
5 a successor is appointed, and such member may be reappointed after a
6 two-year absence from the Commission. The Governor shall fill all
7 vacancies and unexpired terms in the same manner as the original
8 appointment of the member whose position is to be filled. No
9 initial appointment to a term of less than four (4) years or any
10 partial-term appointment to fill a vacancy or unexpired term of
11 another member shall be counted for purposes of determining term
12 limits. An appointed member may be removed by the Governor for
13 cause.
14 D. Whenever a member of the Commission is absent from more than
15 one-half (1/2) of all meetings of the governing body, regular and
16 special, held within any period of twelve (12) consecutive months,
17 the member shall thereupon cease to hold office by operation of law.
18 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1000.23, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 1000.23. A. The Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
21 Commission shall have the power and the duty to review and adopt all
22 building codes and standards for residential and commercial
23 construction to be used by all entities within this state. Codes
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2085 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 and standards adopted by the Commission shall be the minimum
2 standards for residential and commercial construction in this state.
3 B. All public projects shall abide by such minimum standards
4 and requirements; provided, nothing in the Oklahoma Uniform Building
5 Code Commission Act shall prevent or take away from state agencies
6 the authority to enact and enforce requirements containing higher
7 standards and requirements than such minimum standards and
8 requirements.
9 C. Municipalities and other political subdivisions shall abide
10 by such minimum standards and requirements; provided, nothing in the
11 Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission Act shall prevent or take
12 away from such municipalities and other political subdivisions the
13 authority to enact and enforce requirements containing higher
14 standards and requirements than such minimum standards and
15 requirements.
16 D. The Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission shall have the
17 power and duty to establish a continuing education and training and
18 certification process for all residential and commercial building
19 construction industry personnel affected by the codes adopted by the
20 Commission, including, but not limited to, code inspectors
21 officials, design professionals, and trade workers. The Commission
22 shall establish regional training for the purpose of training the
23 county and municipal inspectors in the Uniform Building Code. The
24 regional training shall be offered at no cost to the participant
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2085 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 stat e-licensed building code officials and shall be funded from the
2 funds received pursuant to Section 1000.25 of this title. A fee may
3 be assessed to all participants other than state-licensed code
4 officials. When assessed, the fee shall be limited to any cost
5 directly associated with the training and shall be remitted to the
6 State Treasury pursuant to the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
7 Commission Act. Such fees shall be deposited in the Oklahoma
8 Uniform Building Code Commission Revolving Fund and shall be used
9 solely for the purposes of the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
10 Commission Act. Each inspector code official operating in this
11 state on behalf of any state agency or any municipal or county
12 office may complete regional training and be issued a certification
13 for inspections certificate of completion by the Oklahoma Uniform
14 Building Code Commission on and after January 1, 2015. The training
15 and certification applications, qualifications and procedures shall
16 be promulgated by rules of the Commission. The Commission may
17 establish forms and procedures to implement and administer the
18 provisions of this section.
19 E. The Commission shall establish a workforce development
20 process with the purpose of increasing the number of available code
21 officials in Oklahoma. The Commission shall promulgate rules on the
22 workforce development applications, qualifications, forms, and
23 procedures to implement and administer the provisions of this
24 section.
